Flippy - An Othello/Reversi Game in Python & Pygame

Released under a "Simplified BSD" license

This game can run with both Python 2 and Python 3. This game is featured in the book "Making Games with Python & Pygame" by Al Sweigart. This book is released under a Creative Commons licenses and can be downloaded from http://inventwithpython.com/pygame

Game Instructions:

Place your tile so that your opponent's tiles are in between your new tile and one of your existing tiles. These opponent tiles are then flipped to become your tiles. The game ends when all the possible spaces have been taken.

Click on Hints to have the game show you all possible moves you can make.